The paper deals with the problem of encoding a private source of information and a public correlated source into an index such that an eavesdropper can retrieve very little information about the private source. This problem falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of side information and the optimal encoding in special cases, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of leakage of information, which is a topic in data security (cs.DS).
